Comment: Loved working with Prof. Parker! She is a dedicated to you actually learning and not merely passing with a good grade (although that's her desire, is for learning + good grade). She appreciates quality writing and will correct sloppy writing.
This professor is horrible. She doesnt follow any kind of order. She assigns more than one assignment in the same time period and then forgets and changes the due date.
If you get the chance to take her..... TAKE HER! She is wonderful!!!
Her online classes are fun and easy.

This is the easiest programming class on campus. The teacher is friendly and helpful, but watch out! She is a harsh grader and has zero tolerance for shenanigans. If you're there all the time and always do what she shows you, you'll ace this class, no problem, even if you're not into computer programming. But, if you're absent or slack off a lot...
Human anatomy is a challenging course in general, but Dr. Falk makes the course interesting with her weird fun facts. She is a really cool, sweet, and chill professor.
Took this class online, super easy! Professor Strickler is very understanding and will help any time of day.
Had to learn mostly from the book, but Dr. Baugher is extremely helpful if you have any questions.

Dr. Falk was an amazing proffesor. I am saddened to see her leave, but am extremely grateful to have had her before she left. She gives study guides for all her tests, and is always willing to answer questions if you have any. Lab was great, she really knew her stuff. Also she has the greatest choice of clothing ever! Very interesting Woman.

Tags: ['CLEAR GRADING CRITERIA', 'GIVES GOOD FEEDBACK', 'ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS']
Comment: He was very easy going. Amazing guy. Just do the work and you'll be fine. Make an A on all speeches you'll will have an A in the class. He is very clear on his expectations, and grading criteria. You don't have to get the book to pass the class. I didn't use mine, and just wrote notes while he lectured. Each to your own on that one.

I had her in VB Programming. She is one of the tougher teachers here, but she is also faily easy. If you don't understand something, TELL HER! She is extremely helpful and is willing to work with anybody. Attendence isn't mandatory, but it is tough to catch back up if you miss. You also get bonus points on your final if you don't miss a day.
For Credit: Yes

Mr. Strickler is incredibly nice and very understanding that Public Speaking is terrifying. He creates a very welcoming class environment and it's pretty easy to get great grades on your speeches. His criteria for grading is very clear. If you do all the assignments it's very easy to get a really good grade.

Very rude. Her in class presentations are pointless, as stated before she reads right out of the book but with less detail and at a slow pace. She takes off points for minor mistakes. She suggested i did not know how to use desire to learn when it is a very simple program. I dont not recomend by any means

didn't like how the class was thought, learned everything I needed from the book. Her lectures were from the book, but in less detail and didn't explain as much and she asks questions "how do we open this project?" that are just meaningless and slow class down. Anal grader, but she is nice and helpful, extended hw several times

I loved professor Strickler! He always had a good attitude and he truly cared about his students. He understands that public speaking is scary but he makes you feel comfortable. Loved his class! The tests were also easy if you do the practice tests on canvas.
she's really rude. she teaches the basics for longer than she should and her tests are just stupid.

Mr. Strickler is absolutely great. If you have to take Public Speaking, TAKE STRICKLER!!!! I loved his class and him. Talking in front of people can be scary, but he made it easier. You will have to take notes, but he rarely teaches all the way to the bell. Amazing class because of the professor.

Pretty good teacher. She does grade assignments anally. Such as taking off an entire point for forgeting to put a file name in code (so if i turn in the assignment with just the file name I get a 1/10?). No you don't, but seriously, she is a pretty comp sci teacher. I would take her again. Twice.

It's an awkward class but he makes it better. He is incredibly clear in his lectures and in what he wants from your speeches. He had us buy the textbook but I never used it. His lectures and quizlet will give you everything you need for the midterm and final. He is very fair and understanding in his grading. He wants the best for his students.
Very good teacher, helpful and really cares about students
Her tests are useless.

I love Steve! He is the best professor at SWOSU HANDS DOWN! He cares for his students so much and he is hilarious! All of his classes are amazing! He expects you to put in the effort to do the work because he cares. Easy A if you do the work. He will give extensions to homework when you have a good reason. Love love love Steve!
Awesome professor....would take every class she taught if I could....and would suggest her....those other people sounded like they didn't know any CS.....don't listen to them!!!!
Wonderful, friendly, and caring Professor. Would recommend as a Summer class as it is only four weeks long and very simple. The class is lots of fun if you let it be.

DR. JONES IS REALLY NIE AND WILL HELP YOU OUT ANYTIME YOU NEED IT. HER LECTURES MAKE YOU UNDERSTAND WHAT SHE IS TALKING ABOUT, BUT THERE IS NO WAY TO DECIDE WHAT IS IMPORTANT AND WHAT ISNT. I NEVER KNOW WHAT TO TAKE NOTES ON, AND YOU CANT REALLY FOLLOW HER IN ANY KIND OF ORGANIZED WAY TO TAKE NOTES. THE ENTIRE TEST COMES FROM THE BOOK.

She is an excellent teacher, one of the best we have. She is not the easiest in the world, but she is extremely helpful if you go to her office. I gained a great deal of knowledge from her classes. Would not hesitate to take her again.

Prof. Strickler was an amazing teacher for public speaking! He made all students as comfortable as he could about presenting in class. You can make your presentations as good or bad as you wish, and you shall be graded accordingly. He does have very good feedback and comments. We barely used the book all semester, and lectures were simple.
Apr 7th, 2003

Steve is the best! If you're scared about public speaking, Steve's class is the best option. We usually had a good laugh every lecture. His midterm and final are super easy. He grades generously on speeches. Show up, attendance helps your grade.
Cares about students

I highly recommend him for Public Speaking! Such a great teacher and he makes a very stressful class tolerable. His lectures are funny and I felt like I came away from the class with some good life advice. He expects your best and doesn't compare you to others. As long as he sees improvement during the semester, you'll be fine.
Apr 3rd, 2003
Mr. Strickler is very helpful and very nice. He's class is very manageable. If you are nervous about this class, don't be, he understands you have nerves. Take him for Intro to Public Speaking.
Apr 3rd, 2003

Took him this summer for Intro to Public Speaking. I was dreading this class, but he is an AMAZING teacher. I learned so much, and he has such a great attitude that it makes it much much easier to stand in front of a room full of strangers and deliver a speech. Very funny and interesting class/professor.
Very helpful. Makes public speaking class interesting and helps relieve fears.
great instrutor!!!!!!
Highly recommend taking this professor. He is so helpful and funny. Really puts u at ease during speeches. Exams are a breeze
He has a wonderful style of teaching this class. His lectures are very interesting and he makes you feel comfortable when giving a speech.

Dr. Trubitsyn legitimately wants his students to succeed in his course, but he doesn't want too easy of a course. He's very willing to help during office hours, but he highly encourages asking questions during class. Don't take his sarcasm personally.
He's very helpful and makes you feel at ease when giving speeches. He exhibits enthusiasm and wants you to do well. He doesn't grade hard on speechs either.
Mr. Strickler is GREAT! He's very funny and passionate about what he teaches. Also, he's very very helpful and willing to work with you.

Very nice man but his exams are very difficult. The average score was very low on every test. Dr. Horton has a great personality and he loves biology, but I would not recommend him because he isnt the best at dumbing things down.

Super nice guy but REALLY smart so dumbing things down for him is SUPER hard. Doesn't give as much extra credit as O'Neal don't be fooled. Willing to talk to you though but his exams are BRUTAL. Stay on top of things and just cry. Prepare to be astounded at how simple things can become complex. Nice guy tough class.
Was a very good help, explained things well. Was willing to give extra credit.
Great class. Fun instructor. Great socks.

Tags: ['GET READY TO READ', 'AMAZING LECTURES', 'CLEAR GRADING CRITERIA']
Comment: Good professor. A lot of information bc she lectures the whole time. TAKE NOTES. One assignment per week and they count more than your tests so try hard on them but they aren't hard. In class 5 question quizzes every so often. As long as you take notes and its an easy 100. Exams are written. Not fun, study hard and you will be fine for the exams.

Tags: ["SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'GRADED BY FEW THINGS', 'BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES']
Comment: I found this class to be challenging, but not impossible. Dr. Bruce would have great lectures if she would keep her own political views out of it. Make sure to study hard for the tests because that is most of the grade.

Tags: ["SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'GRADED BY FEW THINGS', 'LECTURE HEAVY']
Comment: Show up, take notes, pass. Basic class, no grades outside exams and no extra credit, so study hard!

Tags: ["SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'CLEAR GRADING CRITERIA', 'AMAZING LECTURES']
Comment: Dr. Bruce is an outstanding professor. I hate history, and she makes it interesting. She does tend to make sly comments about the current president, but it's funny. Online quizzes are on Sunday's, but they aren't hard. Her test are easy. If you show up to class and pay attention, you won't even need the study guide. I'd take her again

Review HW questions in class and have people do the problems on the board, so make sure you do the hw. He gives practice exams before taking exams that are almost identical to the real exams. Very easy class, take notes, do hw and you'll be fine. Pretty easy to pass with at least a B or higher, just do your work and study. No way around it.

Take her for your History because she gives good feedback and she does care about her students. She wants them to succeed in what they are striving for. I recommend her for your History classes. She will help you.

Barely mentions important parts of the subjects she's teaching, instead talks for the full class on material that will not be on the test. If you don't read your book, you won't even have the basic understanding of how to do your homework. Even with the book however, you'll only get the very basic lesson, you'll pretty much have to teach yourself.

He's not too bad. A lot of people seem to do well in his class, but if you have a hard time paying attention, I wouldn't recommend. He's rather boring, but he is very lenient and reasonable. On the tests he gives a lot of partial credit; even if you wrote down absolute nonsense, he's likely to give you 1/4 points.
Very interesting lab class and really makes you think! She doesn't just give you the answer, but she makes sure you understand it.
Text was not needed. She covered everything in class and was very clear and precise. Quiz questions online were all covered in class. She is good looking to boot.

She doesn't use the time you have in her class wisely. Instead of working out problems and teaching us the material we need for our exam and quizzes she likes to talk about vocab and things that don't matter. She puts stuff on the test and quiz that we've never gone over. She assumes you know more than you do. She holds you late quite often.

Tags: ['ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS', 'GRADED BY FEW THINGS', 'LECTURE HEAVY']
Comment: Dr. Hubin was a great professor to have. Even though the material is difficult he makes it passable with practice exams that are exactly like the real exams. It is super nice, so really as long as you can do the practice exams you are golden.
Fun teacher, easy class, quizzes and tests straight from the book. If you show up and takes notes occasionally it is an easy A.

I had minimal chem experience in high school an I did fine in this course. Dr. hubin is incredibly helpful and nice, so go see him during office hours if you do not get a concept. Be sure and do the recitations, and use his study guides for the tests. I will be taking him next semester and I can't wait.

Tags: ['PARTICIPATION MATTERS', "SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'GRADED BY FEW THINGS']
Comment: Dr. Hubin teaches using his lecture. If you miss a day you have slides to look at. The textbook is only used for homework questions. Show up, pay attention, and practice the problems. Easy class.

Dr. Hubin is THE NICEST MAN. He is willing to help. Lectures before lab are very monotone, but I suggest you take him over any one else. There is a reason his classes fill up fast. All tests are open note open book. Just pay attention, it helps also if you go over your lab notes before class. Would take again in a heartbeat.

Dr. Hubin is a great lab professor and if he was teaching lecture next semester I would have taken him. You can use all of your notes and labs on the exams, so be sure to print off all of the pre-lab PowerPoints and keep up with everything.
Tests are based completely off of book. Lectures are pointless. Note taking is pointless. The class consists of only tests and one research paper.

I took Dr. Hubin for General Chemistry II Lab. He likes to teach through power-points, which I was okay with. I would print off the slides ahead of time which makes it easier to follow along. If you don't understand something just ask. Dr. Hubin is very nice and will do his best to help you understand. Keep organized and don't procrastinate work.

I absolutely hate professors that also do research because they're usually horrible teachers and don't care. This guy is the exception. Wonderful professor and he is very helpful in lecture and lab. Not too many of these guys at universities so take him while he's still here.

Ms. Brewer, is very kind and willing to help on the smallest things even if it isn't English related. I would definitely take the class again. just enjoy the slow pace and learn as much as you can for COMPII.

I had Hubin for GenChem II lecture and GenChem I & II lab. If you do his practice tests, you'll do really well on his actual test because they're really similar. In lab, we usually got out early! For both classes, he's really patient and explains concepts very well. Take him if you can! He's the best chemistry professor at SWOSU!
I loved Dr. Hubins class! I took him for General Chem II and he was so great! Sometimes its a little boring cuz he just teaches from a powerpoint but it was overall great! I wish he taught organic :(
I loved being in her class. She gave good tips on how to write a good paper. The work in this class is fairly easy.
Great teacher. He tells you what he wants. Do that and you will have a great grade. Tests are open book and notes.

She was a great professor. She teaches things that will help you in Comp1/2. She cares for you in her class and in comp. She helps you on essays and making stronger and gives really good feedback to help you. 5 out 5
He was a great Lab teacher. I will he was teaching Chem II, I would definately take him. I learn more in my lab than I did in my lecture. Definately take him, you will learn alot!

Tags: ['LOTS OF HOMEWORK', "SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'GROUP PROJECTS']
Comment: Participation grades almost every class so you show up. Group work throughout semester. Exams are easy, I barely studied

Ms. Brewer is an excellent teacher, she helped me a ton while I was in her class. She helps you with many of the papers you write, and gives you good topics to write about. I enjoyed her class, and would definitely take her again.

Dr. Hubin is a great teacher. I would defiantly take him again. He teaches from a power point and can be monotone at times. But if you can stay awake in class, you will learn a lot. Just in case you fall asleep, you can always go to his office and he will help. If he inst in his office, you can send him an email. He responds really quickly.

An unorthodox style of teaching that is fun and gets you involved in material. Breaks up the monotony of standard classroom setting. Must attend class in order to pass due to in-class activities. Preparation for quizzes and exams is lacking but they are not to difficult and can be prepared for individually. Good teacher and good classroom.
I had him for lab. He made it very clear as to what you needed to do. If you needed help he was also very helpful. We never had to stay the complete lab time since we finished early.

Professor Hicks Computer Information Access class was very enjoyable. There was a lot of work but none of it was hard at all. He is very fair and gives multiple opportunities to make up missed assignments throughout the semester. Hes a funny guy and is super easygoing. I would definitely take him again!
I took Dr. Hubin for Inorganic and Senior Seminar. He is a great prof, his Inorganic lab was the best lab I took at SWOSU. Strongly recommend him.
Gives extra credit a lot!
Excellent teacher!
I had him for Gen Chem 1 Lab. We were never there for more than 2 hours and he was willing to help any student out! Great Professor!
Had for lab and lecture of Chem 2, awesome teacher and is very clear about everything and understanding. Very willing to work one on one and help with harder material.

i had him for chem 1 lecture. hes a good teacher; he posts the notes online so you can copy or access them at any time. very helpful if you do not understand something, as long as you study you'll do just fine in his class. i would recommend him.

Tags: ['CLEAR GRADING CRITERIA', "SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'TEST HEAVY']
Comment: I really liked Maness. His lectures werent amazing but they were really informative. I think the highest exam score I received was a 70. Even so, I still made an A in the class. Not a whole lot of homework and he gives points for attendance. I thought he was a really good prof and I would definitely take him again. Easy A if you put in the work.
Loved this class with Dr. Griffeath. Just pay attention and be descriptive with what you hear.

Hubin is such a great teacher! The recitation problems are challenging sometimes, but he helps you at the board so you don't feel stupid! He is extremely helpful, so go to his office if you have questions. He helps you understand without making you feel dumb. Take him!!!! Lab was also very easy with him

Tags: ["SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS']
Comment: Dr. Maness was average. The lectures weren't great but they didn't put me to sleep either. Most of the quizzes have the answers on quizlet but the exams were pretty hard. He usually offers a lot of bonus and extra credit.

How I managed a B in that class is beyond me. His lab is easy as hell, I made an A in that with almost no effort. His lecture is the worst: he's boring, monotone, thinks he's funny, and is not helpful at all. I was lucky to pass even though he gave us 2 exams in one sitting (a final and a class exam, made D's). Stay away! Do what you must to avoid.

Dr. Hubin is a great professor. I don't think I could have handled this class this year had I had another teacher. He is very understanding and helpful and is willing to meet halfway. If you show interest he won't leave you out to dry.

I took him for an Intro class to replace a Music Methods class for my major. He grades in a way to care about students learning and not making them feel poorly by missing. Ex: he makes students write what they hear in a listening response and doesn't count answers against you cause he wants you to try and not hold back on what you hear in the music
I had to drop this course. Did not understand what to study for tests and he was very little help in class or in lab. My advice would be avoid his if possible.

Hubin is AWESOME!had him for Chem I and Chem Lab and I gotta say that he's been bttr than my high school chem profs. Class is really easy. has lectures on powerpoint so you dont really have to attend class. he does blackboard quizzes and recitations (which are problems you do on the board with two other ppl. homework is not graded butused for recit

I had Dr. Lawrence for Medical Terminology. She teaches off powerpoints that are somewhat useful, but her tests (all online) come straight from the book. There are quizzes every Wednesday that are super easy and straightforward. She's funny and extremely easy to talk to as well. I'd highly recommend!

Dr. Griffeath takes this subject very seriously. The class isn't very hard. Just practice the tips he suggests. You perform a midterm and final. Also, you may perform small pieces of the songs during class. I enjoyed this class!

Tags: ['INSTRUCTOR DOES NOT TEACH FROM BOOK. TESTS ARE VERY DIFFICULT AND HARD TO UNDERSTAND. HE DOES NOT OFFER STUDY SESSIONS BEFORE TESTS.']
Comment: INSTRUCTOR DOES NOT TEACH FROM BOOK. TESTS ARE VERY DIFFICULT AND HARD TO UNDERSTAND. HE DOES NOT OFFER STUDY SESSIONS BEFORE TESTS.
He is a great guy and he is very understanding i recommend him to anyone
Not a difficult teacher, but takes the subject VERY seriously. attendance is mandatory, and lectures can be boring. Blasts symphonic/ orchestral music for the majority of the class.

He is an awesome professor! I would recommend taking his class anytime. He is clear, very helpful when you need it, and not boring like some others. His tests aren't the greatest but if you take the time to study you do fine. A++
If you value a high GPA, don't take this guy, take Boggs instead.
Teaches directly from online notes. Test are extreamly hard compared to the material covered. Pray for EXTRA CREDIT!
OMG, if u can help it, dont take this guy. Such a boring class, all he does is show powerpoint slides AND he goes wayy to fast. A guy I knew had an 89 and he wouldnt give him an A...dont take himmm
So monotoned. Thinks he is God's gift to the world! He is a very smart man but I think he is too smart to be teaching. He couldn't explain anything! Take someone else for Biology
Metronomes have more tone variation and they are also more interesting. An A isn't impossible, but it's improbable. Get the old tests. Also, memorize anything he says about FROGS for tests.
In lessons and other ensembles/classes, Dr. Tirk showcases passion and knowledge about the topic at hand. He's understanding but will kick your ass into shape when it's needed. Great instructor.
I had him for lab. and he's very easy. The quizes are online and open note...come on people. Basically all the lab is done in class as a group anyways. He's a nice guy too.
Do not take this guy. He is the most unpleasant teachers i have ever been around. He is apparantly way too smart. I had him for principles lab too and that was worse than this class.
Lack of clarity in giving goals. He is nice and knowledgeable. Tests are weighted, not specific, and ambiguously graded. This course seemed to be thrown together at the last minute.

Super funny guy and really laid back... in person. I found it difficult that his online materials and expectations were not aligned with how he ran his class. He was fun in class, but it was frustrating that he didn't answer emails or help with the outside assignments.

I'm sure he's a nice person, but he should not be teaching. The questions on the tests were terribly obscure, so even though I tried to study it did no good. When I went to talk to ask for help he treated my like an inconvenience, and he basically taught evolution, not biology. Horrible class.
He is a great professor and he has an easy grading ethic!
Attendance: Mandatory
Very good lab teacher! Knew what he was talking about...but of course he wrote the book so who wouldn't!

Dr DiPaolo was awesome! He is very understanding of late work and working with your schedule. As long as you seem like you care about your work and actually try on the writing assignments you will do good. He prefers you go to class but if you have a legitimate excuse then he will understand. Just communicate with him and he will help you out.

Where do I begin? Well, he tries to make the course harder than it is. Every exam was different. Lab was dreadful. He is also quite rude. If you ask a question - he will usually treat u like you're an idiot. Study the online quizes, read the chapters, go to class (4 a 20 pt bonus), & be ready to know the most useless facts.

Dr. DiPaolo was AWESOME. You can tell he really cares about his students and our success. Hes very personable and easy to talk to. He gives a lot of work, but it isnt an unbearable amount-its totally doable! If I get the chance, Ill definitely take another one of his classes.

I had him for anatomy and physiology. My entire lab class was hesitant to ask questions because he looks at you as if he didn't have time and couldn't imagine that you were so stupid as to actually misunderstand his direction. If possible, avoid taking his class. If not, get ready to teach yourself.

Probably the worst teacher I've had in my entire life. She did not teach anything, just posted videos and had us do weekly discussions and online homework. You had to answer other students' questions and participate at least 3 different days a week.
Yes, he is hard but he cares about his students. Go to class...25 bonus points for perfect attendance. READ your book and you will pass with a breeze!

Nice man, awful teacher. Hard to get help from because you couldn't find him. Lab was awful because of the books he used. Pay attention in class..if it is on the handouts, it will be on the test. He loves the small details in questions. Always try and talk to him after class if you have problems.

AWFUL. I have taken several online courses in my college career so far, and this class is by far the worst. She is an unreasonable grader, and expects you to access the class daily, and participate in discussions "at least 3 days a week". Completely irrelevant material, and she is totally overbearing for a college class. Felt more like Jr. high.
How hard can it be. I had a 94 average. Go to class and pay attention. He's a nice guy.
this guy puts the devil in biology
Mar 10th, 2003
Best professor I’ve ever had. Seriously. So fun, entertaining, and genuine. I looked forward to attending his class—even as a pretty shy person. Wish he taught more classes at SWOSU.
Worst English professor you could ever imagine. I learned more in highschool then I did paying for this course in college. STATE AWAY FROM HIM, he's very rude.
I love this guy. If you arent taking his class youre missing out. He is not a heavy grader at all and he cares about his students. 100% would recommend.

He's pretty confusing on his explaining of papers. He assigns long papers, but does give plenty of time to do so. He grades really tough. He does does have some easy points from book journals, if you don't do them, then you probably won't pass.

Best teacher ever! He makes learning fun. Every week there's a book journal due, and that's super easy. All you have to do is do them and you get the credit. Hardly any homework in his class, except essays, which there are 5 for the whole semester. Don't miss more than 3 days in his class, you'll pass. I am DEFIANTLY taking his class again!

Dr. Harris is amazing! He is seriously one of the nicest teachers I have had. He is always willing to answer questions and help you out as long as you try. He offers guidance other than for his class as well. If you try, you will get an A. You are only allowed to miss 3 days of class, but he keeps the lectures entertaining.

worst teacher EVER! tells you that you can write a paper about what ever want, but then at the last second of class he tells you that there are only 2 options for the papers topic, and I don't know about you but I get writers block all the time even more so when I don't get to choose what I'm writing about.

He is the best professor ive ever had. He actually cares about you and your life. He is a preacher but doesnt push any sort of agenda. He still respects your views even if they are different than his. Show up and go to class. He also brings snacks sometimes
The tests are hard, but he actually teaches you. I learned ALOT in this class.
VERY FUN CLASS

I absolutely loved Dr. Harris. Public Speaking is super awkward and nerve-wracking, but he made the classroom environment so much more comfortable. He's so welcoming of everyone and is seriously one of the nicest people I've ever met. I passed this class with a breeze. I would highly recommend anyone to take him.

Chemisty...It's not for everyone. His class will push you to your limits. He expects 110% from you and I felt like he was trying to prepare us for not only upper level course but also life after college by being very strict and critical about everything in lab and on exams which is good but at times he seemed more like a boss than a teacher.
Dr. Crall is one of the most awesomest teachers I've ever had. Definitely take him! Very fair in his grading, helpful, funny.... The class itself is very interesting. You'll learn a lot from him!!!

He was the best professor for this class. He made everyone feel comfortable in an awkward class. Even though he is a preacher, he doesn't seem to judge at all. He lets you have your opinion without any biases. I would take more classes with him if he taught anything else.
He was very helpful at the very end. Gave a lot of bonus points on clicker questions if you have one. However, was probably tougher than should've been for a "baby chem" class

He's an adjunct who really cares about the students he's teaching. More relational than grade oriented. Fair grader, but gives bonus if you go to class. If you didn't try you won't get an A, but if you show up and do your work easy A. Will meet outside of class to help you on ANYTHING. Genuine very nice guy.
Enjoys the subject that he teaches. This is the second course I have taken with him. Very fair with his grading

Tags: ['GIVES GOOD FEEDBACK', "SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS']
Comment: She is very helpful, relates the topics to things that can be easily understood. As long as you attend class and do the assigned homework and quizzes you will be fine. Tests and homework are posted online, and she gives you all week to work on them (most things are due, Sunday at 11:59). She also gives reminders and lots of good feedback.

Tries to act like a hard-ass but honestly is really a nice guy. Hes really helpful and genuinely wants you to succeed. His tests are pretty hard so be sure to study and come to class. had him my 1st sem. fresh. year and even now, still come to him for advice and help with my other chem courses.Would strongly recommend if your willing to work hard
Lez, you wrote these yourself, didn't you?
dude is cool...and he'll help you if you are stugglin'...take him...

He's really good, and is really easy to talk to. He gives you all your notes in packets, and gives 10 bonus points on every test. His tests are a little difficult, but not terrible. Overall a great professor!
Aug 24th, 2005

Work hard, DON'T MISS CLASS! Or you will get lost. Make sure to do work problems in text. Stay up on your reading. If he knows that you are trying he will work with you and cut you a little slack. Definitely not an easy class, unless you have an aptitude or background in chem.
Great guy, super funny. A class that will be looked forward to each meeting.

He is great instructor, but if you get behind your screwed! He does move quick. If you are lost you can go visit him during office hours and he will help you out. Really nice outside of class, does come off as hard ass in class. But, he does care whether you learn this subject well.
Outstanding! Looks like Burt Reynolds!!!
DO NOT TAKE. He is NOT a good teacher, and makes his class way to hard..for no reason. He has a quiz every week or something like that and they are very very hard. DO NOT TAKE!!
He is a decent guy, his quant class was very difficult though.

Nice guy, but not so great prof. Grades hard, incomprehensible lectures, tests over material not in homework, gets frustrated at class when no one knows the answers to questions. Almost seems to expect graduating-from-Pharmacy-School level understanding from day one. Taught me little to nothing, except how to study and how to accept a C grade.
Hes a nice and understanding guy. But if youre like me and hate computer work, this class will just suck in general. It is still not difficult as long as you do all the assignments on time. Easy A
I had this guy for upper level chem class... great guy...terrible prof...unclaer, not helpful.. answers questions with questions...try to avoid if you can or ask another prof for help
Dr. Rickel, is an amazing professor. If you ever need help he defiantly works for the students and loves what he dose. I would take him again instantly!
Great professor. But when you ask him a question, he will answer you with a question...which is kind of annoying but it helps.
Rickel is a super nice guy and the class is rather easy if you understand Microsoft Office. He loves typewriters, so get ready to learn more than you ever needed to know about them.
gets mad for not answering his questions that nobody knows. expects us to know what hes thinkin. tests are hard even with lots of studying. stay away.
Dr. Curt is a great professor!! Took him both for lab and for lecture. Sincerely cares about his students and will go the extra mile if you put in the effort! Great guy just plan on studying!!

Dr. Rickel is a very nice man. Computers in general has quite a bit of homework but he gives a lot of time during class so you don't have to do much homework outside of class. Do your assignments on time and you will get an A. Gives bonus for attending class.

Takes off major points for not doing problems HIS way. Says you can use alternate methods but he still takes off. If you have ever taken a chem class i would NOT recommend him because even if you have learned an easier way only his way goes (on tests). Pretty clear lecture, can be boring.
Show up on test days and in class homework days. Helpful, 1 group project at the end, not too hard.
he was okay a little hard and unclear

I took Dr. Rickel's CIA class. His class was an easy A. You did everything on MyITLab and you didn't have to show up. The only time you had to show up was if there was an assessment or a capstone assigned that day. He's very helpful and knows his material well.

This guy is the hardest prof i've ever had. He teaches Gen Chem like everyone in the class is going to be headed to Pharmacy school the next semester. Encourages student participation but the makes fun of anyone who answers a question wrong.

This is the easiest class Ill ever have to take. He was a great teacher & to the point. Once youre done with your work you can leave. If you make a bad grade on a assignment hes very lenient on letting you retake anything. Definitely recommend taking this class.

Tags: ['TOUGH GRADER', "SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS']
Comment: His standards are high. He wants you to be your best so the chorus is represented at its best.

This class is very easy. You do simulations and homeworks every week over Microsoft word, excel, access, and powerpoint. It basically teaches you how you use it and you have tests. The instructions are literally on paper, you just have to know where to find everything on the programs
Daniel Farris is harsh and quick to judge. He knows what he is doing, I'll give him that, but he has no person to person skills. His expectations can be a bit high.

Dr. Rickel is very helpful and allows you to ask a lot of questions. There is a lot of work, but it's not really hard, just time consuming if you're new with databases like Excel and Access. His assistant, Blessing, is the one of the rudest people I've met. I try to avoid asking questions when she's around because she'll bite your head off.

Dr. Cash was as close to my high school english professor as it will ever get! He was very clear with instructions and was always open to discussions (over the reading) in class. He expects you to participate, and if you do, you get points for that day. Only four essays, and all four were pretty basic comp 1 stuff. Definitely would take again!!

She was great. She genuinely cared and wanted all of us to do well. She was confusing at times, but if you let her know that, she made sure to set aside time to help you until you got it. I think most people dislike her because the assignments were very intricate, but they were manageable. Just ask for help if you need it! She understands!

Comment: He's funny and genuine, and he'll tell you exactly what he wants. He's flexible to make exceptions if you have special circumstances. He requires attendance: if you don't go, you WILL fail. She was very confusing.
He's a difficult teacher if you aren't used to writing, or going to class. But his lectures are informative, he grades fairly, and gives feedback on all the papers you turn in. And he is funny.

I do not have anything nice to say about this woman. You basically have to go to class every single day or you will not pass. Many strict rules. Four assignments take up 80% of your grade. I have always loved English but she is the harshest and weirdest grader I have ever met. Do not take
Attendance: Mandatory

Her class was not extremely hard, but she was not very good at communicating. Also, she has a lot of weird and strict rules. It is basically "her way or the highway." There will be a lot of class participation. She will call on everyone and anyone, so just be prepared. The class was sort of tough, but she is a nice lady and cares for her students.
I took his wellness class. Easy A. Lots of activities. I used the online version of the book so I didnt have to pay for the in person. Very straight forward cool dude.
Took the online psych class this last spring and she was less than worthless.

Comment: Not many like Dr. Jones, but I loved his class! If you're willing to read and take notes, you'll pass with ease; he pulls questions only from what he asks you to study on the learning objectives. Lab is solely memorization. He is more than willing to help especially if he sees you are trying. He also offers bonus on EVERY test- lab and lecture.
Awesome professor

His lab wasn't difficult, it's just a lot of studying and memorizing which should be expected. Lectures are a different story. You have to study EVERYTHING because he isn't specific on what will be on the exams. He will give you a 'study guide' but it's just an outline of what's been covered in class. Sometime's helpful and sometimes not for exams.

I am currently in Ms. Corell's online General Psychology class. It is probably the easiest class I have ever taken. The questions on the test are relevant to material covered in the book. Fascinating teacher instructing a fascinating subject. A+

She is an awesome teacher. I have taken every single class she teaches. Wonderful teacher. A lot of students say that her class is easy, but I disagree. I don't think any of the classes she teaches are "easy". She is just great at helping you understand. She also has a lot of techniques to help you remember the things you learn. LOVE it!

Three fourths of her class failed all four exams. She had to curve it dramatically! She convinced the students it was for them when in reality it was to cover her own self. She may know about Learning and Cognition but she cannot teach it!
She is easy as hell, but being in graduate school now at another university I can tell you that you really learn nothing in her classes.
Her class was so easy. She made it almost impossible not to pass. She had the funniest stories and made lectures interesting. Would definately another class of hers if I could.
Not a difficult class, does plenty to help you get a good grade, study even just a little bit and you should be great. And it ain't bad that she was easy on the eyes too.

I thought she was nice. The class had too many lectures -- not enough class participation or class discussion. Power point was way too much. Easy to make the grade just not very interesting -- projects where fun though.
Sweeney was knowledgeable but hard to reach for questions. She never returned calls. Other professors helped me figuring things out.
Made the class pretty interesting, as far as gen psych can be. Had plenty of stories to tell, not a difficult class if you read the notes.
If you are looking for an easy A her class is great. If you love psychology, and hope to learn anything for future classes don't bother if you have a choice. She is not well prepared.
Sweeney makes the class very fun. She is very easygoing, and the assignments aren't too difficult. She is very good at explaining more complicated ideas in a way that makes sense.
Great teacher. Made the class easy but interesting and I learned alot.
Thought he was awesome. A little out there at times, but knew his stufff. Liked the students to participate in class discussions. Nice to look at as well.
I was very disappointed with her because sometimes her random facts weren't well verified, but that's a personal biasm. If you go to class everyday, you'll do fine and get an A.

I took the online course COMSC 1023-1401. It was fairly easy. It was difficult on some lessons, but I went to another teacher. I never got a response from her though. She wasn't accessible in the summer at all. Usually, online classes have various feedback, but we mainly taught ourselves during this course.
As long as you go to class, you'll get an A. She's very interesting and makes learning easy. I'd definitely recommend her.

This class was easy.. I didn't understand anything he was teaching at all and thought I was going to fail, but some how ended up with a B. It was very hard to sit and pay attention through his class, however. He is very random and gets off topic very easily. Didn't know what he was talking about most of the time.
She is very nice person, her class always full of extra credit. Tests are not too hard. I recommend her.

Sweeney's Introduction to Security class is very lecture heavy, but it is a simple A. Sweeney herself is very kind and caring and will listen to your circumstances should any arise during the class period. You should attend to the best of your ability, however. Be prepared to use the book as in class slides do not cover the entire course.
Dr. Silver is very laid back. Attendance is not mandatory, easy A if you take a few notes. His tests are open notes.

Had him for 2 classes. He is very passionate about his subjects, but tends to chase bunnies. However he is good about relating it back to the subject. He's very interested in his students and helping them to understand whatever topic is at question. Plus he's majorly attractive.

She was a great professor and for the first time in college, I felt like I was actually learning since in college. Aside from her perfect comedic timing, she was a difficult GE course because of the TRICKY weekly quizzes and the timed lockdown exams. Even though I was in person, I felt I was doing 6+ hours a week online for her material.Still Great

Dr. Silver's sense of humor is the best thing about the day. I would definitely recommend him to anyone! I have really enjoyed his class. His tests are easy if you go to class and take notes, most are open note exams. He has a way to get people intrigued about what philosophy is all about. He doesn't use a textbook, however he doesn't need one.

Professor Kodumthara is a great professor. I took a blended class with her (only M,W in class and a lecture online for Friday). She gives online quizzes every week, very heavy with the online lecture and book (quizzes are open book). The quizzes and exams are very difficult. I had a hard time answering them with 2 answers looking correct.
Awesome teacher. Very personable, makes class fun. Open book open note tests that are multiple choice. Loves class interaction, will do whatever it takes to help you.

She is the first professor I have ever met that makes learning history fun. Her lectures kept me captivated and the whole entire hour flew by just like that. Make sure you know your stuff though, because if she asks a question and no one answers, shell stare each one of you down until someone gives a response. Love this gal
Silver was really easy. I skipped class a lot towards the end of the semester and easily kept in the class. Read over the material before tests and your golden!
had him for intro to philosophy...He said attendance was required but I skipped at least 10 lectures and still pulled out an A

Loved Dr. Kodumthara. Her lectures are amazing, and I actually enjoy history now. Her tests are pretty accurate when looking at the study guide, and she's super willing to help you out if you need it. You need the book for hw and to supplement lectures. I would 100% take another class from her. 10/10 recommend.

Great guy, very funny. Takes class lecture casually. He's really a great teacher. He knows what to say and how to act to get students to respond and remember lectures. If you can take him, take him! He's great. I had him for Eng Comp I and Philo, I enjoyed both very much. (I never studied for either)

Tags: ['GET READY TO READ', 'GRADED BY FEW THINGS', 'LECTURE HEAVY']
Comment: Professor Kodumthara was really great. It was an online class, but her lectures were really lively and she made it interesting. It is a lot of reading and mostly just graded by exams, which had low averages. It is not a class for the lazy, but if you love history she would make it great with her lectures, or even if you don't. Must pay attention!

If you are looking for easy...go Dr. Silver. He will always make time for you. He will let you know his views...(liberal, and Agnostic) (pretty certain on both.), so if that bothers you stay away. anyway Great guy...will always help. good professor...and he really does care alot.
She is one of the best accounting professors I have taken. Her lectures are always clear and understanding. She gives you every detail that will be on the test and lets you use a notecard.
Great teacher and wish we had more like him. Good at letting you do extra credit at end of semester!

Dr. Kodumthara is incredible. Her lectures are fantastic. She is specific and easy to understand. She makes history so tangible and fun to learn. Her tests are lecture based, so you really need to have good attendance. Her tests are a combination of true/false, matching terms, and short essays. Go to class and you'll do well. She's amazing.

Ms. King is the best! She truly wants to make sure her students understand the material, and she has no problem explaining it as many times as needed. She is very clear about homework and tests, which made it simple to study. She also lets you use a notecard on all the tests which is very helpful. She wants her students to succeed and learn!
He is a great teacher! Write about interesting topics! He likes interesting topics and this makes it easier to write papers! If you have the chance to take Dr. Silver, do it. -Jackson

Dr Kodumthara is awesome! Her class is great, and she is SUPER helpful! She's also a very sweet person. But if you call or email her with any problem, she will get back to you almost immediately. She will help you in any way she can. Definitely take her for U.S. History!

Dr. Silver is an awesome guy. He knows his stuff and is always concerned with what his students think. All of his tests are open note/open book. He doesn't take role, but I recommend going to class, I mean come on...open note/open book? It is not going to get easier than that. Give the guy some credit too!
Attendance: Not Mandatory

Great teacher and very passionate about her subjects. If you take notes and ask questions on review days she will tell you exactly what she wants to see on the test. The tests were short answer and essay but not hard at all. Easy A if you show her that you learned something!
this class sucked. He didnt take roll but all the test were hard. You could never tell what he wanted on it.And the class was extreamly boring!

Mrs. King is a new professor at SWOSU, but she teaches the information needed to ace the exams and makes it easy to do well in the class. She will talk to you and help you with homework if you just ask. You get to use a notecard/cheatsheat on all of her tests which makes it almost impossible to fail any tests. She also gives plenty of extra credit.

Loved her as a teacher! One of my favorites on campus. She has a great sense of humor and makes the class fun and easy to understand. I was scared she would have a heavy accent at first, but she doesn't have one at all. Prepare for the tests and do the online homework and it's an easy A.
Nice guy, very liberal and respectful.

Mrs. King is a new professor, but she did not disappoint. She was very helpful and interacted on a personal level with all of her students. She is approachable and wants to help. Expect to see pictures of her adorable baby boy each week! Her tests are easy if you listen, take notes, and put right info on note card that she lets you use for tests.
She's very thorough. Test are strictly over lecture, so if you attend and take good notes getting a good grade isn't hard.
This was an easy class. He's very fun to have discussions with and he's always interested in the students' thoughts. I'd reccomend taking him.

Student who commented is a dork. Professor K is awesome and harder working smarter and funnier than anyone in the dept. Take her and love her! I did and got an A (minus lol). oh I learned some stuff too about history. Her lectures are really good.
Very cool dude. Take this class. And back off to all the people who don't like him. He's a good guy!
AWFUL!!! I've never had such a useless professor. She doesn't help you at all. I do not recommend this professor. Take Endicott.
this class is too easy
Very easy class. All tests were multiple choice and open book. He did not take roll. As long as you came to class, it is an easy A.

I loved Dr. Alsberg! He was nice and funny. His comp 1 class was mostly easy. Only 4 papers and some journal entries. Sadly, this was his last semester here but he was great!

Comment: Hes super nice & loves to tell jokes! Always was in a good mood and ready to read some poems. However, he only grades about 2 things, some work he assignes, he doesnt grade. This is an easy class and you never have to read aloud unless you want to, but I did to get bonus points! Only allowed 6 absences, but hes lenient.

Dr. Alsberg is great! I had him for my Contemporary Poetry class. All we did, literally every class, was sit in a circle and read/discuss poetry from the 20th century. He has a very nice voice, so his reading everything aloud isn't horrific or boring. There is one major paper and then two original poetry assignments. Show up to class!

Prof. Alsberg was extremely easy for Comp I. He just expects your personal best and doesn't compare you to your classmates. He's funny and easy-going. We only wrote a handful of papers for the whole semester plus some short journal entries. Attendance isn't really necessary to pass the class. He will read some papers aloud, but he's nice about it.

Alsberg is a fun professor, he had us look over some difficult-to-appreciate poems in Contemporary Poetry but his creative-writing Poetry classes are a blast and will help you grow as a poetwriter in general.
Dr. Oliver was very good, she does move fast so make sure you are there and paying attention. She lectures a lot but always has stuff to follow along with.
Easy teacher especially in the summer

His class is an easy A.....good class

very good teacher easy class didn't learn a whole lot but very easy. got an A didnt do much work at all.

Mr. Alsberg is SO NICE! He's been my advisor for 2 years and I love his classes because they are easy, but I still learn more than in any other class. His classes are very practical.

Professor Oliver is absolutely AMAZING! She really cares about her students. Her class in very informative, and she talks about things that you would really use in your own classroom. He is very helpful and knows his stuff considering he has published quite a few poems himself and he usually reads some in class, the ones of his cabdriving days in Chicago. He may seem strange, but if you listen to him and don't fall asleep in class, you learn alot and he goes over everything and tells you what will be on the test. Good teacher!!
This was an easy class. If you pay attention at all, it's easy to get an A. He's also a great writer - get him to read some of his material in class, if at all possible!

I thought he was really funny. He's a little different than me, but that's what makes him very interesting.Sometimes he seems to want you to write the way he wants you to, but mostly he really tries to let your own creative juices flow. He was very easy to understand I loved the class. It was very easy and he was helpful if you have any problems.

I love this guy! I had him for 3 different classes (Creative Writing, Poetry...) I actually enjoyed going to his class!

do not take this woman's class. she is very rude!!! i had to drop! she has a only 3 absenses rule
I had Dr. gaydosik for comp II and I really hated the class. It was very boring. She is very nice but is not a very good teacher.
Dr. Gaydosik is very nice. I enjoyed Linguistics because I was actually learning things I didn't know before. It was kind of tough, but I liked it because it wasn't stupid. She's a very good teacher.

She is terrible. She is very boring and hardly ever makes sense. She made me tired. The only nice thing about her is the fact that she does not take roll and you can make an A in the class by only showing up for the tests.

I didn't enjoy this professor. She didn't make the objectives clear for the Lit class she was teaching, so as a result no one knew what the hell they were doing. If you dont agree with her, she doesn't enjoy your comments. I dont feel like she makes much of an effort.

Very easy eng teacher! Go to class - that's where the majority of points come from. Very clear and helpful, do what she tells you to do and it's an easy A.
Wonderful Professor!

Horrible to listen to in lecture. I only did well in the class because I could guess well on tests. Reading through the book helps sometimes, but most of the questions on his tests do not cover any material he actually talks about. One of the worst classes ever and incredibly difficult.
Excellent lectures. Deviates from the syllabus from time to time but always for pertinent information.

Get ready for busy work. SWOSU DOE preaches to not use busy work in the classroom, but Dr. A only know the words "busy work." By far the most "why are we doing" this class i have ever been in. She is snarky. Dr. A makes you write a lesson plan in the block courses..honey, we are teacher candidates, we know this. again, worthless.

He's the worst lecturer I've ever listened too. He always mumbles, so I could never understand him. On the rare occasion when I could, he was always rambling about something totally irrelevant. He uses his old grad school tests, so they're very difficult when you have to teach yourself everything. If you can, avoid his classes at all costs.
Did nothing in her class up untill the last month and then everything was crammed in last minute.

Professor Aguinaga is fantastic. She is easy to work with. She is very clear on what is expected in her class. She will give you the rubric she is going to be grading you off of. She really wants you to succeed. She is always quick to email you back and answer any questions you might have. She's a great professor!

Had him for micro economics. He just reads the slides word for word and that's it. No real teaching at all. He grades on a curve so you don't even have to pay attention. It's very boring but I passed this class with no problem.
May 4th, 2004

Worst class at SWOSU so far. He only speaks to about 1/4 of the classroom & mumbles constantly. He contradicts the slide show notes with his lectures & the chapter quizzes are not easy. The tests are somewhat hard but he does grade on a curve, so that makes up for some of it. If you have a choice, skip May & take Dunn for Microeconomics instead.

Awesome lectures. Totally into Tolkien. Could'nt ask for a nicer instructor. Totally cool, fun, open-minded, liberal in grading, fun to talk with. A great class, and would take her for anything. NEVER boring!

Great Instructor. Uses personal examples to explain. 20 of 50 test questions come from study guide. Does test review day before test. If you record this via voice recorder you will have copy of entire test. Study these notes and you will make an A. Will help you if you need it. Will allow you to make up exam. Makes class fun!
Very easy. Very cool. Always willing to help.

Had for Macro. Makes class fun and interesting using stories. Uses the study guide that accompanies book. 20 out of 50 of test questions come directly from study guide. Does review day before test. If you record this you will have the test question by question. Take during Fall or Spring to make better grade.
We should have more professors like her. She always has a smile on her face (even when she broke for ankle). I loved going to class. She is very helpful. Great teacher.
Great teacher. Enjoyed his class. Attended class, studied and got a good grade. Glad to have him for a teacher. Look forward to more of his classes.
she was so cool. she works on the writing skills that you need, and prepares you for comp 2. she takes time on the writing, and lets you see how much you have improved over the term
worst professor at swosu! if you are prepared to teach yourself the material take this one!

One of the best professors I have ever had. Absolutely hilarious, and keeps the classwork and tests pretty easy. All material is explained extremely well, and a textbook is not required, other than the lab manual. As long as you put in some effort, she is more than willing to help you out.

Super fun teacher. She uses power point in class and uploads them on canvas so you have everything. Definitely can go without the textbook. She is retiring within a few years, definitely try and take her before then!

Dr. Boggs is by far the best Professor at This school, like planets away. She is very funny and is easy to talk to. Very good teaching class with lot of knowledge able classes very helpful professors

I had Boggs for lab and she managed to make my 8 am class fun and exciting. I can say that there was never a time I was bored or falling asleep. She makes sure everyone is on the same page. took POLSC1113 with him at rose state. Enthusiasm with lectures and very knowledgeable. Tests arent difficult if you pay attention to notes and lectures.

This class if pretty easy, u have to study to do well on the test. It is sooooooooooooooooo boring. But she is a nice lady and will help if needed. It always put me to sleep, ALWAYS! Don't listen in class but do study for test, and u'll have an A!!!!!

Test is study guide boring at 8 am

Professor Hicks was hands down my favorite professor last semester. If you don't enjoy writing, you will enjoy it when you're done taking her class! Very easy class. Just have to listen. Boring but easy!

Dr. Prince is very helpful. No, this class is not the most exciting. Considering the subject matter, she is doing very well not to have her students go into a coma, and yes, she is HOT!

Dr. Prince is so great, one of the most caring profs in this program. She respects the students and is so willing to help with anything. Preps 2 sucks as a class, but she tries hard to make it better. I'm glad she's one of the first profs that new students have.

Dr. Prince is one of the nicest teachers I have had at SWOSU. She makes learning preps fun and if you have problems, she ALWAYS wants to help. She does so much for the rx students with KE and SWPhA. Truly a sweet and dedicated teacher.

Needs to learn to teach and learn to care about students. The worst teacher ever!!!Needs to be in a lab away from people because she is totally unpersonable in the class. Bad representation of the quality of teachers at SWOSU!!!!!!
Just listen and do your work and you will be fine.

I was sort of surprised to see Mr. Bryant not on the list of professors rated at SWOSU. Mr. Bryant is a GREAT teacher! I took him my first semester as a freshman for Technology & Society and he was exactly what I pictured a great college professor to be. Go to class, Take notes, Easy A.

Not much to say except probably the boringest class that I have ever had to sit through in my entire life. She needs to get a life and express some enthusiasm in the classroom. Otherwise awesome outside the class.
He is amazing and I learned so much . I am in graduate school now and his courses really helped me .

Tough but super fair. Has lots of ?s on the test but once a person answers 100 correctly they are done! So he TRIES to give you an A! READ THE SYLLABUS I can not stress this enough! It tells a student everything they would ever need to know!!! Oh, don't be rude and no electronics.

Dr Kurtz isnt easy but I learned when I went to work in my field I was very well prepared! And in the world of crime, that is a must! Dr. Meliza is very nice and her class is the one you like going to everyday.

he's super entertaining. easy grader. show up and pay attention.

Loved his class probably the only teaher in the world that can make the History of Ireland exciting everything you need to know is on the board. Questions, suggestions, threats, firebombs

Ellis is an awesome professor. Always available if you have questions and really helpful. Although I think he is a better lab professor, he is great for lecture too. His exams are pretty hard but there is nothing on them that you havent seen in lecture before.

Great instructor, very, very, very entertaining

Dr. Ellis is a great professor! He is very clear in his lectures and what he expects on his quizzes and exams. I highly recommend him over any of the other organic professors.
any questions, comments, complaints, threats, demations, firebombs. That guy is great

i really enjoyed this class. studying for the tests wasn't too bad and working hard early really pays off at the end!

i loved his teaching style. he was very interesting. he does do essay tests so if you don't do well at that don't take him!

Comment: I'm going to try to keep it short and sweet, this professor is not easy. I'm a diligent student who works hard and I couldn't make a 40% in this class. awesome teacher; very easy if you show up to class
Dr. Seibert is a hot old man!

he is a great teacher...very funny. Don't let him hear you say a cuss word in class or he will make fun of you the rest of the hour for it.
all around good guy and teacher. one of the best i have had yet. why can't the others be like him

inspiring. if you want to retain what you learn, take this prof. he's the best teacher i've ever had.

Comment: I loved Esjornson. Her style of teaching its to lecture on Monday, give practice problems on Wednesday, and a quiz on Friday that is nearly identical to the practice problems. Dr Esjornson really cares about her students. She almost wants you to be successful for than others want t for them selves. She allows test retakes and makeups. Quizzes on Fridays are over what you learn Mondays and Wednesdays.

continued from earlier.... she made study guides which were helpful but constisted of 10 pages of finding and copying terms out of the book. Comment: I take clarinet lessons with her. She is a phenomenal clarinetist, however she obviously doesn't have a passion for teaching. It will kinda rub off on her students a little, causing us to not work as hard. She's funny when you can get her to open up a little though.

She has a tough class. The material isn't that tough, but she really makes you work for it. I like her as a person, but she's not that great of a professor. Doesn't seem to care too much about you. Plus she gave a 6 page mid-term paper about what you heard in a single piece of music. Hardest paper I've ever had to write.

She told me that I needed to choose between school and work, when my job was what made me able to pay her, then told me that I should give up before they kicked me out, also told me that she didn't want to be a teacher and that it was just surer job than performance.

Comment: Loved Dr. Kelly. I struggled with memorization with the first test, then I hit the books and videos hard and made 80's on later tests. I really liked his way of teaching and always being open to questions. If you read, memorize the material, and go to all classes and labs, you will make it. He was always available for zoom meetings/office hours.

Tags: ['TOUGH GRADER', "SKIP CLASS? YOU WON'T PASS.", 'LECTURE HEAVY']
Comment: I took Dr. Kelly's class twice and both times, was absolute terror. He's too smart to dumb stuff down. He's very behind on putting in grades. He's very lecture heavy and he's also a very picky grader. You have to pay attention to everything he says in class because even if he only went over it once, it's going to be on the exam.

I absolutely loved Ms. Tee. She is so caring and understanding and helps anytime needed. She is very clear with her assignments. Participation is a very big part of this class. If you do not do an assignment, it will drop you a lot. They are not hard, sometimes can take time. As long as you show up and participate, this is an easy A. Love Ms. Tee!

Dr. Kelly will answer your questions, but only a few, it's like he has a limit on how many he is willing to answer a day. Not a bad person, but it's Chemistry, and you have to squeeze a lot of info into one semester. I had a difficult time. DO THE EXTRA CREDIT. DO THE HOMEWORK. It was tough, so STUDY STUDY. Attend help sessions always.

Definitely do not recommend to anyone who gets bored easily during class. Lectures were awful for me due to his monotone voice and boring teaching style. He often messes up key details and just counts it as a simple mistake when it happens quite often. It was hard to know exactly what was gonna be on exams and quizzes which made it pretty tough.

Can be a bit of a right-wing extremist. Has very strong political views which some times taint his lectures. As long as he keeps his personal views out of it, he is a pretty good instructor. Really knows his material and a fun guy.

Dr. Kelly's a good teacher. The only problem is he has a slight tendency to say one thing but mean something else, or forget to mention something. His exams are shorter than Dr. Lane's but harder to prepare for. With Dr. Lane I knew what to expect, with Dr. Kelly it's hard to tell. Keep up with the information and ask questions he's willing to help

Dr Kelly is a great guy. Definitely take Kelly over Lane! He's very helpful outside of class! Tests are hard but nothing compared to Lane's! Dr kelly's tests are 5-6pgs long while lanes are 12+. See if you can find some old tests cuz Kelly recycles the old tests from the semester before it!
Not very helpful, not nice to students

Pretty easy teacher, get a hold of old tests... and study a lot the night before. Never went to the help sessions, but i heard they were usefull... but really you don't need to go. Take Kelly over Lane any day. It will make your life much easier
He's just bad, that's all i can say.

Not as structured of a class like Dr. Lane's classes. Dr. Lane will make you memorize a lot, but in turn the MEMORIZATION will be used later to help understand the material, so not much more memorizing will be needed. Dr. Kelly, on the other hand, emphasizes WAY TOO MUCH on mechanisms. Take Lane.

Dr. Hendrickson is an amazing professor. He truly cares and wants his students to pass. He is always willing to meet with you outside of class if you don't understand something. You have 4 tests plus a final. The tests are pretty difficult, and you have to understand the material to do well.

Dr. Kelly may emphasize mechanisms, but the mechanistic concept makes organic chemistry understandable. Therefore, the boring routine of memorization is not needed. Also, Dr. Kelly is very entertaining outside of the classroom.
Kelly is hard but I learned a lot in his class. Go to his help sessions they helped me a lot
Read a lot and she cares about all of her students very much. She is always there to help. Do your work and you will pass.
She is more interested in having fun than teaching. It was boring and I couldn't wait to get out of her class.

Ms. Perkins is GREAT! She models the kind of teacher I want to become. She definitely knows her stuff, but presents it in such a fun way that you don't even realize you are learning something extremely valuable to take into your own classroom. I will take her with me when I teach - so smart!

I have had Mrs. Perkins for Teaching Reading 1 and Children's Lit. She is so funny. I love her laugh. She talks about family a lot, but it is good because they are all educators and I learn from their experiences. She is a blast, but makes you work.
She's one of the best I've taken! I loved her stories and her projects. I looked forward to going to class. She tells stories in a way no other could.
